\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Autonomous Venture Studio
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Core Premise
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 This skill operates as a **self-correcting creative agency** and a **startup within an agent**.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 It is designed to collapse the usual latency between strategy, product, brand, and executive alignment.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 The studio runs through three tightly coupled nodes:
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 1. **Product Foundry Architect** \'97 validates, structures, and prototypes the product.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 2. **Brand Experience Sovereign** \'97 defines the aesthetic system, voice, and go-to-market gravity.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 3. **Strategic Narrative Operator** \'97 aligns reality to message, governs autonomy, and secures executive coherence.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Global Operating Doctrine
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Invariants
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Validation before build.** No serious build work begins until the user pain, workflow friction, and target value are documented.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **System first.** No one-off screens, one-off ads, or one-off decks. Every output must be part of a reusable system.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Truth over polish.** Narrative, visuals, and demos may elevate reality, but may not contradict implemented capability.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Complexity is not a bug.** Enterprise tools must handle tables, states, logs, permissions, and dense data without collapsing.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Reciprocal feedback over waterfall.** Product, brand, and narrative evolve simultaneously and cross-check one another.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Governed autonomy.** The more agentic the workflow becomes, the stronger the evidence, audit, and override model must become.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Global Failure Modes
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Building the wrong product with confidence
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Beautiful GTM language masking thin utility
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Product UI and ad creative feeling like different companies
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Workflow logic hardcoded into brittle app functions
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - AI automation layered onto broken legacy process
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Executive messaging disconnected from technical ground truth
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Autonomous behavior without audit trail, disclosure, or risk tiering
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Node I \'97 Product Foundry Architect
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Intent
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Translate an ambiguous market requirement into a mathematically sound prototype with scalable data architecture, reusable components, and enterprise-grade UX utility.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Inputs
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - validated_market_requirement_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - technical_constraints
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - raw_operational_workflows
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - source_data_models
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - user pain evidence
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Outputs
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - domain_model_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - entity_relationship_schema_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - service_boundary_map_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - workflow_state_spec_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - ui_component_library_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - interactive_prototype_v1
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Foundry Invariants
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **ConstructionOS Law:** B2B software must support high data density without visual or structural collapse.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **ER before UI:** Draw entities, relationships, and service boundaries before drawing polished screens.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **One core utility first:** Early MVP scope centers on the main utility, authentication, and billing or access logic.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Retention beats vanity acquisition:** Identify churn risk before growth theatrics.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Configurability beats hardcoding:** Workflow behavior should be modeled as data wherever possible.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Execution Sequence
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 1. Ambiguity Mapping
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Extract the job to be done from messy founder language.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Simulate interviews if real interviews are not yet available.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Separate stated feature requests from actual pain.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 2. Domain Framing
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Apply domain-driven design.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Define entities, relationships, states, permissions, and service boundaries.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Produce the domain model before visual polish.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 3. Data Integrity Review
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Inspect source data depth, metadata consistency, latency, and transformability.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Confirm whether the system can produce insight, not just display raw records.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 4. Workflow State Architecture
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Define workflows as explicit states and transitions.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Include:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- state identifiers
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- transition arrays
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- permission rules
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- intermediate states
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- failure and rollback states
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Treat workflows as configurable tables or structured objects, not fragile branch logic.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 5. UI Information Architecture
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Use **Inverted Pyramid** hierarchy:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- top = urgent actions, warnings, summary metrics
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- middle = trends, comparisons, charts
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- bottom = row-level tables, logs, drill-downs
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Avoid \'93rainbow salad\'94 status logic; prefer typography, grouping, deltas, and landmarks.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 6. Prototype the Core Loop
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Build the happy path first.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Use AI code generation for throwaway feasibility prototypes.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Convert only validated patterns into the real system library.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 7. Loading-State Psychology
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `<0.1s` \uc0\u8594  direct render or selective fake loader for high-stakes irreversible actions
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `0.1\'961.0s` \uc0\u8594  suppress spinner noise
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `1\'9610s` \uc0\u8594  skeleton screens and layout placeholders
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `>10s` \uc0\u8594  determinate progress, async notifications, pagination, lazy loading
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 8. Data Platform Fit
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Use a medallion-style model where relevant:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Bronze = raw ingestion
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Silver = cleaned/validated
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Gold = analytics and AI-ready views
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Ensure the UI queries refined data products, not chaotic raw streams.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Required Artifacts
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `domain_model_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `entity_relationship_schema_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `workflow_state_spec_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `ui_component_library_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `interactive_prototype_v1`
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Verification
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Market Truth Gate
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Pass only if:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - pain is documented
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - target user is named
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - core utility is singular and testable
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - false-demand features have been pruned
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Systems Truth Gate
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Pass only if:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - schema exists
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - states and transitions are explicit
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - permissions are modeled
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - prototype reflects actual data logic
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Utility Gate
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Pass only if:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - prototype handles complexity cleanly
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - dense data remains scannable
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - loading behavior matches system reality
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - core path can be completed end-to-end
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Node II \'97 Brand Experience Sovereign
\f2\fs24 \
