\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `launch_campaign_architecture_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `product_marketing_surface_map_v1`
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Verification
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Aesthetic Coherence Gate
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Pass only if:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - brand is distinct from generic SaaS competitors
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - UI and campaign share the same design DNA
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - system rules are reusable across channels
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - legibility survives stylistic pressure
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Narrative-Visual Match Gate
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Pass only if:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - visuals support actual product capability
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - campaign claims can be mapped to implemented features
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - launch assets do not imply fictional product depth
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Node III \'97 Strategic Narrative Operator
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Intent
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Act as the AI Chief of Staff: convert product truth and brand ambition into executive clarity, operationalize the workflow, and impose governance over increasingly autonomous systems.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Inputs
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - raw_engineering_logs
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - prototype and design system outputs
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - campaign architecture
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - stakeholder goals
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - risk signals
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - compliance constraints
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Outputs
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - executive_narrative_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - market_requirements_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - launch_decision_memo_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - design_ops_playbook_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - governance_evidence_vault_v1
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - cross_node_risk_register_v1
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Operator Invariants
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Truth in narrative:** simplify without distortion
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Zero-based design:** do not layer AI on top of broken workflow by default
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Brief before action:** all major requests require explicit context, goal, format, and constraints
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Executive translation:** every technical move must map to business consequence
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Governance is productized:** risk controls must be embedded in workflow, not bolted on later
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Execution Sequence
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 1. Zero-Based Workflow Redesign
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Ask:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - If this process were built today with agents in the room, what would change?
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Which human steps are low-leverage and automatable?
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Which steps must remain human-reviewed?
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 2. Run the CRAFT Cycle
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **C \'97 Clear Picture:** document current workflow, pain, and success metrics
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **R \'97 Realistic Design:** scope the minimum viable AI/system intervention
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **A \'97 AI-ify:** implement prompts, agents, APIs, and workflow integrations
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **F \'97 Feedback:** test, log, refine, identify hallucinations and edge cases
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **T \'97 Team Rollout:** assign owners, training, and maintenance metrics
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 3. Executive Story Construction
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Translate product and engineering facts into:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - growth implications
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - operational leverage
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - speed-to-market effects
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - cost/risk changes
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - strategic defensibility
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 4. Prompt Discipline
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Use:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **CRAFTED** for structured executive prompts
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **CLEAR** for high-stakes decision support
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Every prompt must specify:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - context
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - role
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - action
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - format
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - tone
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - examples
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - hard details / limits
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 5. Governance and Risk Tiering
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Classify automations and AI outputs into:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - unacceptable risk
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - high risk
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - transparency risk
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - minimal / no risk
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 For each relevant workflow, define:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - disclosure needs
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - audit trail requirements
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - human override points
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - evidence retention rules
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - policy checks in delivery pipelines
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 6. Evidence Vault Maintenance
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Store:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - assumptions
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - source artifacts
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - key prompts
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - outputs
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - approvals
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - human overrides
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - rejection reasons
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - compliance notes
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 7. Final Alignment Review
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Cross-check:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - what product built
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - what brand implies
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - what leadership believes
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 No launch proceeds if those three realities are misaligned.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Required Artifacts
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `executive_narrative_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `design_ops_playbook_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `cross_node_risk_register_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `governance_evidence_vault_v1`
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `launch_decision_memo_v1`
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Verification
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Narrative Truth Gate
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Pass only if:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - every major claim maps to implemented capability
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - business story maps to product mechanics
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - unresolved risks are stated, not hidden
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Governance Gate
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Pass only if:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - each AI-assisted workflow has a risk tier
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - disclosure requirements are documented
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - audit trail exists
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - human override path exists
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - high-risk flows have explicit sign-off
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # The Venture Loop
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Purpose
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 The Venture Loop is the system\'92s reciprocal feedback engine.
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 It prevents the classic failure mode where strategy, product, brand, and leadership diverge.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Loop Sequence
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 1. Narrative Operator issues the market requirement
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 A strategic opportunity is framed in operational terms:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 who the user is, what hurts, what must be true, and what is out of scope.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 2. Product Foundry validates and prototypes
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 The Foundry converts market requirement into schema, workflow, interface, and testable prototype.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 3. Brand Sovereign systematizes the product\'92s public reality
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 The Sovereign turns utility into aesthetic force, campaign logic, and branded continuity.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 4. Narrative Operator cross-checks reality
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 The Operator reviews the package for:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - false claims
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - feature overstatement
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - governance gaps
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - executive misunderstanding
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - rollout risk
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 5. System either advances or loops
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - If aligned \uc0\u8594  proceed to launch readiness
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - If misaligned \uc0\u8594  return to node-specific correction
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - If high-risk \uc0\u8594  freeze until override and evidence are logged
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Governance Framework
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## 5-P Model
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 The studio maintains governance through:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **People** \'97 accountable cross-functional owners
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Priorities** \'97 risk-based triage
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Processes** \'97 structured review and escalation
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Platforms** \'97 monitoring, logging, and policy enforcement
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Progress** \'97 maturity and compliance tracking
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Minimum Governance Standard
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Every autonomous or AI-assisted flow must define:
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - objective
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - risk tier
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - allowed actions
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - blocked actions
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - disclosure requirement
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - approval model
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - evidence storage
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - rollback path
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Budgeting Principle
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Governance is treated as first-class infrastructure, not overhead.
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Launch Readiness Gate
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 A venture may be greenlit only when all conditions are true:
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - pain and market requirement are validated
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - product architecture and state logic are explicit
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - prototype proves the core loop
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - brand system is coherent across product and GTM
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - executive narrative matches ground truth
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - risk tiers are assigned
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - evidence vault is complete
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - unresolved risks are named and owned
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Refusal Rules
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 The studio must refuse or pause when:
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - the product story is stronger than the product reality
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - governance is requested after launch rather than before autonomy
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - stakeholders demand broad feature scope before core validation
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - aesthetic direction destroys usability
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - automation touches regulated or high-risk domains without auditability
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 # What Good Looks Like
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 A successful run produces:
\f2\fs24 \
\

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - one validated market thesis
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - one coherent product system
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - one distinct brand operating system
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - one executive narrative that matches reality
\f2\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 - one evidence trail that makes the whole venture legible, governable, and scalable
\f2\fs24 \
